name: nedc_run
synopsis: nedc_run [options] file(s)
descr: prints the EDF header for each file

options: none

arguments:
 file(s): individual EDF files or lists of EDF files

examples: 

 nedc_run file1.edf
 nedc_run file1.list
 nedc_run file1.edf file2.list
 
 These demonstrate the different type of arguments that
 can be specified: single file, a list of files, or a mixed
 list of single files and lists.

 Note that this utility is a Python version of nedc_print_header.
